          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "题解",
      "level": 2,
      "blocks": [
        {
          "heading": "贡献法",
          "level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "我们要求的是所有对 $(l, r)$ 的 $\\lfloor \\log_2(\\frac{r}{l}) \\rfloor$ 之和。",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "换个角度想，对于任意非负整数 $X$（比如 $X=3$），它可以看作是由 $3$ 个 $1$ 组成的。也就是说，<strong>一个数的值，等于它大于等于</strong> $k$ ($k=1, 2, 3 \\dots$) <strong>的次数之和。</strong>",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "因此，我们可以把题目要求的求和转化为：<strong>枚举所有的正整数</strong> $k \\ge 1$<strong>，计算有多少对</strong> $(l, r)$ <strong>满足</strong> $\\lfloor \\log_2(\\frac{r}{l}) \\rfloor \\ge k$ <strong>，然后把这些对数全部加起来。</strong>",
              "depth": 1
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "heading": "数学推导",
          "level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "我们来看看这个条件怎么化简：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ \\lfloor \\log_2(\\frac{r}{l}) \\rfloor \\ge k $$",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "因为 $k$ 是整数，所以上面这个式子等价于：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ \\log_2(\\frac{r}{l}) \\ge k $$",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "两边同时变成 2 的指数：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ \\frac{r}{l} \\ge 2^k $$",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "也就是：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ r \\ge l \\cdot 2^k $$",
              "depth": 1
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "heading": "计算合法对数",
          "level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "给定了一个具体的 $k$，我们需要在 $1 \\le l \\le r \\le n$ 的范围内，算出有多少对 $(l, r)$ 满足 $r \\ge l \\cdot 2^k$。",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "我们可以<strong>固定</strong> $l$<strong>，看有多少个合法的</strong> $r$：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "1. 对于给定的 $k$ 和 $l$，$r$ 的最小值是 $l \\cdot 2^k$，$r$ 的最大值是 $n$。",
              "depth": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "2. 所以，满足条件的 $r$ 的个数是：$(n - l \\cdot 2^k + 1)$。",
              "depth": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "3. 那么 $l$ 最多能取到多少呢？为了保证存在合法的 $r \\le n$，必须有 $l \\cdot 2^k \\le n$，即 $l \\le \\lfloor \\frac{n}{2^k} \\rfloor$。",
              "depth": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "令 $m = \\lfloor \\frac{n}{2^k} \\rfloor$，对于固定的 $k$，满足条件的 $(l, r)$ 的总对数就是对所有的 $l$ 累加：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ \\sum_{l=1}^{m} (n - l \\cdot 2^k + 1) $$",
              "depth": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "html": "展开：",
              "depth": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ = \\sum_{l=1}^{m} (n + 1) - 2^k \\sum_{l=1}^{m} l $$",
              "depth": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "math",
              "latex": "$$ = m(n+1) - 2^k \\cdot \\frac{m(m+1)}{2} $$",
              "depth": 2
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "代码",
      "level": 2,
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "code",
          "lang": "cpp",
          "code": "void solve(int CASE)\n{\n\tll n; cin >> n;\n\tll ans = 0;\n\tfa(k, 1, (ll)log2(n)) {\n\t\t// n - i * 2^k + 1\n\t\tll m = n / (1ll << k);\n\t\tll sum1 = (n + 1) * m;\n\t\tll sum2 = (m + 1) * m / 2 * (1ll << k);\n\t\tans += sum1 - sum2;\n\t}\n\tcout << ans << endl;\n\treturn;\n}",
          "depth": 1
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
